            "tab_title": "Sleep",
            "heading": "Open Nose. Deep [[ Sleep ]]",
            "heading_tag": "h3",
            "description": "Block the nose, and the body fights for air all night. In a Mayo Clinic study, healthy adults forced to breathe through the mouth saw sleep apnea events surge from 1.5 to 43 per hour — a 29-fold spike. Clear the nose, and sleep does what it was built to do. Quietly. Deeply.",
            "quote": "",
