            "tab_title": "Immunity",
            "heading": "Nasal Breathing: A First [[ Defense ]]",
            "heading_tag": "h3",
            "description": "Your sinuses are quietly making medicine. Each nasal breath carries nitric oxide — a gas that sweeps the airway, accelerates cilia, and kills inhaled bacteria and viruses on contact. In one study, NO levels in the nose ran 100 times higher than in the mouth. Breathe through it. Let it work.",
            "quote": "",
